WEBVTT

00:00:30.726 --> 00:00:33.511
-[TIRES SCREECHING]
-[CAR HORN HONKING]

00:00:33.685 --> 00:00:35.687
[SOBS]

00:00:36.645 --> 00:00:37.689
[GRUNTS]

00:00:49.788 --> 00:00:50.963
[CAR HORN HONKING]

00:00:56.273 --> 00:00:57.274
[TIRES SCREECHING]

00:00:59.450 --> 00:01:01.844
-[GASPS]
-[CRASHES]

00:01:07.371 --> 00:01:09.243
ALMA: I'm so bored of living.

00:01:10.592 --> 00:01:14.683
I wake up every morning
in the same bed
with the same person.

00:01:14.857 --> 00:01:16.206
I shower.

00:01:16.380 --> 00:01:17.729
Brush my teeth.

00:01:17.903 --> 00:01:19.122
I get dressed.

00:01:22.169 --> 00:01:24.171
And I eat the same breakfast.

00:01:24.345 --> 00:01:26.521
And then take the same commute to work.

00:01:26.695 --> 00:01:30.829
I'm 28 years old,
and I'm terrified
this is all there is.

00:01:31.003 --> 00:01:34.355
Sometimes, I'll be in the store, and I'll be looking  at two different cans of beans,

00:01:34.529 --> 00:01:35.486
and I'll think,

00:01:35.660 --> 00:01:36.835
"These beans are better."

00:01:37.009 --> 00:01:39.403
"No, these beans are better."

00:01:39.577 --> 00:01:42.319
And then I'll think,  "That's the most boring thought anyone's ever had."

00:01:42.493 --> 00:01:45.714
I mean, God!
Everything is pointless.

00:01:47.237 --> 00:01:49.239
Anyway, what's up with you?

00:01:50.284 --> 00:01:51.807
What's new with me?

00:01:51.981 --> 00:01:55.115
-[CLEARS THROAT] Nothing...
-Great.

00:01:55.289 --> 00:01:57.943
-No... My face is really itchy.
-What, are you getting eczema?

00:01:58.118 --> 00:02:00.816
No, I'm not getting--
Why would you even say that?
Look at my finger.

00:02:00.990 --> 00:02:02.600
Oh, my God!

00:02:02.774 --> 00:02:04.602
Holy shit!

00:02:04.776 --> 00:02:06.778
-Reed Hollingsworth.
-What's wrong with Reed?

00:02:06.952 --> 00:02:08.476
-Nothing. At all.
-Mm-hm.

00:02:08.650 --> 00:02:10.565
He's fine. He's totally fine.

00:02:10.739 --> 00:02:13.176
-Uh-huh.
-And unassuming, and nice.

00:02:13.350 --> 00:02:15.004
He's very nice.

00:02:15.178 --> 00:02:18.094
Well, that's good.
It's a good thing to be nice.

00:02:18.268 --> 00:02:21.663
And his family is really rich,
and well-connected,
and super classist.

00:02:21.837 --> 00:02:23.708
-Oh, they're "classist"?
-And racist.

00:02:23.882 --> 00:02:25.841
This is about the asparagus.

00:02:26.015 --> 00:02:27.625
[IN MATRONLY TEXAN ACCENT]
"Oh, I see we're passing
the asparagus

00:02:27.799 --> 00:02:29.975
counterclockwise tonight--"

00:02:30.150 --> 00:02:31.847
So his mom has an idea
about the proper way to
pass food around a dining table.

00:02:32.021 --> 00:02:33.240
[MIMICS REED'S MOM]
"Is that how they do it
in México?!"

00:02:33.414 --> 00:02:34.763
Maybe she was
legitimately curious.

00:02:34.937 --> 00:02:35.894
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
We're not from Mexico.

00:02:36.068 --> 00:02:38.070
Yeah, but our mom is.

00:02:40.812 --> 00:02:42.727
Do you think Dad
would have liked Reed?

00:02:44.903 --> 00:02:46.340
Yeah, I do, actually.

00:02:48.472 --> 00:02:51.083
And you don't think it's weird
to get married without
Dad there?

00:02:51.258 --> 00:02:52.955
What am I supposed to do,
just never get married?

00:02:53.129 --> 00:02:54.348
ALMA: That's an idea.

00:02:54.522 --> 00:02:56.567
Ladies. Get you another round?

00:02:56.741 --> 00:02:59.570
-Yes, I will have
a Fancy Familiar.
-I don't know what that is.

00:02:59.744 --> 00:03:02.225
It's a Mozambique Samba
just without the sherbet.

00:03:02.399 --> 00:03:04.706
BECCA: [LAUGHING]
You're so stupid. Stop it,
why do you always do that?

00:03:04.880 --> 00:03:07.230
Um, we're gonna have
shots of Patrón, please.

00:03:07.404 --> 00:03:09.232
And don't go far
'cause you're gonna have
to keep fillin' 'em up.

00:03:09.406 --> 00:03:10.842
You got it.

00:03:11.016 --> 00:03:13.149
-Ugh!
-[CHUCKLES]

00:03:13.323 --> 00:03:15.195
And why did you order shots?
You know I'm trying
to drink less.

00:03:15.369 --> 00:03:17.675
Alma, your only sister
just got engaged.
We're doing shots.

00:03:17.849 --> 00:03:21.113
And then I'm going to
make you listen to
the story of how he proposed.

00:03:21.288 --> 00:03:22.941
-Oh, my God.
-It's so romantic.

00:03:23.115 --> 00:03:24.856
I am going to need booze
for this.

00:03:25.030 --> 00:03:25.988
Two shots of Patrón.

00:03:26.162 --> 00:03:27.207
Thank you.

00:03:30.558 --> 00:03:32.342
What?

00:03:32.516 --> 00:03:36.346
To my sister
and her life choices
which... I support.

00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:44.224
[KEYS JANGLING]

00:03:51.796 --> 00:03:53.798
-[PIANO KEYS THUD]
-[SHUSHES]

00:03:56.714 --> 00:03:57.715
[ALMA EXHALES]

00:03:59.587 --> 00:04:01.937
-[ALMA CHUCKLES]
-Hey.

00:04:02.111 --> 00:04:03.155
What are you doing?

00:04:03.330 --> 00:04:04.983
-I'm humping your butt.
-Oh...

00:04:05.157 --> 00:04:06.594
How long you gonna do that?

00:04:06.768 --> 00:04:08.073
Until it annoys you.

00:04:08.248 --> 00:04:10.293
-[SAM LAUGHS]
-I want the mouth.

00:04:10.467 --> 00:04:11.468
[SAM GRUNTS]

00:04:13.209 --> 00:04:15.342
[EXHALES] Hey.

00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:18.736
Hey.

00:04:18.910 --> 00:04:20.999
Can you promise me
that we're not going to be

00:04:21.173 --> 00:04:23.524
like one of those
boring couples who like...

00:04:23.698 --> 00:04:25.482
[SIGHS]

00:04:25.656 --> 00:04:27.354
...gets married and settles down

00:04:27.528 --> 00:04:29.573
and has babies
and is like all happy?

00:04:29.747 --> 00:04:33.055
-[CHUCKLES] Ew, gross. Never.
-Thank you.

00:04:36.885 --> 00:04:38.495
But it wouldn't be
the worst thing
in the world.

00:04:38.669 --> 00:04:40.149
-[ALMA GRUNTS]
-[LAUGHING] No.

00:04:40.323 --> 00:04:42.760
-That's it!
That's the wrong answer!
-No, no.

00:04:42.934 --> 00:04:45.241
-[GRUNTING]
-You're humping me again?

00:04:46.242 --> 00:04:48.157
You're so crazy.

00:04:48.331 --> 00:04:50.202
No, I'm not.

00:04:50.377 --> 00:04:52.901
-I'm not crazy.
-Okay. Sorry. Sorry.

00:04:53.075 --> 00:04:55.425
I just can't do it.

00:04:55.599 --> 00:04:59.081
I can't do the wedding
and the birth announcements

00:04:59.255 --> 00:05:03.825
and the piano lessons
and the matching Halloween
costumes.

00:05:03.999 --> 00:05:07.742
[CHUCKLES] True that,
matching Halloween costumes
are lame.

00:05:07.916 --> 00:05:10.484
-[SIGHS]
-But, what if you went
as Batman

00:05:10.658 --> 00:05:12.137
and I went as Bruce Wayne,

00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:13.617
and then every time
we were together,

00:05:13.791 --> 00:05:17.186
I'll be like, "Batman!
We're in the same room?

00:05:17.360 --> 00:05:20.015
We must totally be
different people, everyone."

00:05:21.408 --> 00:05:23.540
That's a couple's costume.

00:05:23.714 --> 00:05:27.283
No, it's totally different
because one's Batman
and one's Bruce Wayne.

00:05:27.457 --> 00:05:28.676
Two different people.

00:05:28.850 --> 00:05:30.373
Okay.

00:05:30.547 --> 00:05:32.157
[CHUCKLES]

00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:36.074
But for real.
I don't want to settle down.

00:05:36.248 --> 00:05:37.337
Right now.

00:05:38.816 --> 00:05:39.948
Ever.

00:05:41.079 --> 00:05:44.082
-You never know
what's gonna happen.
-No. I know.

00:05:45.214 --> 00:05:48.783
Okay, we won't settle down.

00:05:48.957 --> 00:05:53.570
We'll be vagabonds
or cat burglars

00:05:53.744 --> 00:05:55.180
or hot air balloonists.

00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:58.009
-Yeah!
-[LAUGHS]

00:05:58.183 --> 00:05:59.576
I like that.

00:05:59.750 --> 00:06:00.925
And then we'll settle down
and have kids.

00:06:01.099 --> 00:06:02.927
-What?
-I'm sleeping.

00:06:07.062 --> 00:06:08.759
[ALMA SIGHS]

00:06:08.933 --> 00:06:11.762
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

00:06:13.242 --> 00:06:14.330
What's wrong?

00:06:14.504 --> 00:06:16.245
The room is spinning.

00:06:20.292 --> 00:06:23.948
[MELODIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:36.483 --> 00:06:39.355
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

00:06:43.838 --> 00:06:47.450
Cassie, no! Cassie, we don't--

00:06:47.624 --> 00:06:49.670
Shoot.

00:06:49.844 --> 00:06:51.323
[CASSIE LAUGHS]

00:06:51.498 --> 00:06:53.630
-No. Don't squeeze it. No.
-[CASSIE BLABBERING]

00:06:53.804 --> 00:06:55.415
Is everything okay here?

00:06:55.589 --> 00:06:57.504
Yeah, Cassie's just being
a C. U. N. T.

00:06:57.678 --> 00:07:01.246
Wow. Okay. I... Cassie?
Cassie, do you need a time out?

00:07:01.421 --> 00:07:02.378
-No!
-Right.

00:07:02.552 --> 00:07:03.814
-Seems like you do.
-Yeah.

00:07:03.988 --> 00:07:05.250
-Let's do it. Come on.
-There you go.

00:07:05.425 --> 00:07:07.339
-Come on. Cassie!
-[CASSIE GRUNTING]

00:07:07.514 --> 00:07:10.473
All right, we're gonna sit here
'till you calm down.

00:07:10.647 --> 00:07:12.910
'Cause I get paid to force you
to behave. Pretty weird, right?

00:07:13.084 --> 00:07:16.479
-I don't want a time out!
-It's not so bad.

00:07:16.653 --> 00:07:20.352
Did you know that the Kogi tribe
of Colombia puts their babies
in a dark cave?

00:07:20.527 --> 00:07:23.225
-Yeah, I know that.
-Oh, you really, you know that?

00:07:23.399 --> 00:07:27.882
Well, did you know
they keep those babies
in a dark cave for nine years?

00:07:28.056 --> 00:07:30.058
And as the babies grow,

00:07:30.232 --> 00:07:32.756
they tell them stories
about what the world outside
looks like.

00:07:32.930 --> 00:07:36.412
What trees and birds
and rainbows

00:07:36.586 --> 00:07:39.110
and clouds look like.

00:07:39.284 --> 00:07:43.985
And when the babies come out,
they see those things
for the first time.

00:07:44.159 --> 00:07:46.553
And they are so blown away

00:07:46.727 --> 00:07:48.468
by how much more amazing
the world is

00:07:48.642 --> 00:07:49.730
than they could have ever
imagined,

00:07:49.904 --> 00:07:53.473
that they have
such incredible respect

00:07:53.647 --> 00:07:55.605
for whatever created this place

00:07:55.779 --> 00:07:57.955
and all
of the beautiful creatures
living in it.

00:07:58.129 --> 00:08:00.871
Can you imagine
feeling that way
about anything, Cassie?

00:08:01.045 --> 00:08:02.612
[HUFFS]

00:08:03.657 --> 00:08:05.180
All right. Do you want me
to put you in a dark cave?

00:08:05.354 --> 00:08:07.138
No, you be in the cave.

00:08:07.312 --> 00:08:10.707
Okay, I'll be in the cave, too.

00:08:12.404 --> 00:08:15.712
We'll be in the cave together.

00:08:17.453 --> 00:08:18.802
[WHISPERS] I like this.

00:08:19.803 --> 00:08:20.891
Me, too.

00:08:22.110 --> 00:08:25.200
[MELODIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:32.686 --> 00:08:35.732
CAMILA: Help me find
a cute baby photo of Becca
for her engagement dinner.

00:08:35.906 --> 00:08:37.865
ALMA: That's why I'm here, Mom.

00:08:38.039 --> 00:08:40.998
Look at this one.
After her first haircut.

00:08:41.172 --> 00:08:42.957
Where's the one
where she's toddling
around the market

00:08:43.131 --> 00:08:46.830
in Saint Cristobal
with the apple soda
and laughing?

00:08:47.004 --> 00:08:49.790
She looks like a tiny,
drunken sailor.

00:08:49.964 --> 00:08:51.139
[SIGHS]

00:08:53.837 --> 00:08:55.317
What did you know
about Geraldine?

00:08:57.493 --> 00:09:01.453
Not much.
She was your father's mother
and she died.

00:09:01.628 --> 00:09:05.501
And she got married,
and had three kids,
lost her mind.

00:09:07.416 --> 00:09:08.286
What about this one?

00:09:08.460 --> 00:09:10.811
Great. Love it. Done.

00:09:13.291 --> 00:09:14.292
Where are you going?

00:09:16.033 --> 00:09:17.513
To get some water.

00:09:19.036 --> 00:09:20.821
Are you coming to church
on Sunday?

00:09:20.995 --> 00:09:23.475
Uh, I don't know.
I'm gonna see how I feel.

00:09:23.650 --> 00:09:25.042
[WATER POURING]

00:09:25.216 --> 00:09:28.045
We have a new priest.
I think you'll like him.

00:09:28.219 --> 00:09:29.786
He's into indigenous cultures.

00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:31.962
Like conquering them
and appropriating them, or...

00:09:32.136 --> 00:09:33.834
Studying them.

00:09:34.008 --> 00:09:36.010
Oh, cool. Maybe.

00:09:38.273 --> 00:09:40.580
Are you going to bleach
your upper lip
before Becca's dinner?

00:09:40.754 --> 00:09:42.407
Unbelievable.

00:09:42.582 --> 00:09:44.105
-You just look so pretty
when you try.
-Oh, my God.

00:09:44.279 --> 00:09:45.759
I gotta go, Mom.

00:09:50.328 --> 00:09:51.416
Whoa.

00:09:54.376 --> 00:09:56.204
Is this dad smoking?

00:09:56.378 --> 00:09:57.901
Yeah. He smoked on occasion.

00:09:58.075 --> 00:10:00.338
-Why didn't I know that?
-He didn't want you to.

00:10:00.512 --> 00:10:02.253
-Was he smoking
when he had the accident?
-No.

00:10:02.427 --> 00:10:03.777
-How do you know?
-Because I read
the police report.

00:10:03.951 --> 00:10:05.300
-Can I read it?
-No!

00:10:06.954 --> 00:10:09.260
I don't have it.
It was 20 years ago.

00:10:09.434 --> 00:10:11.219
Are there
any other photos of him
I haven't seen, Mom?

00:10:11.393 --> 00:10:13.134
-No, that's it.
-I'm taking this.

00:10:13.308 --> 00:10:14.875
Fine.

00:10:17.965 --> 00:10:21.055
It's just weird to think
that there's stuff about my dad
I never knew.

00:10:21.229 --> 00:10:23.710
My mom was married
to some other guy before my dad.

00:10:23.884 --> 00:10:25.189
-Really?
-Yeah.

00:10:25.363 --> 00:10:27.888
He had two Pomeranians,
a red sports car,

00:10:28.062 --> 00:10:29.803
and he beat her
until she had to be
hospitalized.

00:10:29.977 --> 00:10:31.674
Oh, my God.

00:10:31.848 --> 00:10:34.329
-When did you find that out?
-After I graduated college.

00:10:34.503 --> 00:10:36.505
I think she didn't want
to, like, mess me up.

00:10:36.679 --> 00:10:38.115
But once I got that diploma,

00:10:38.289 --> 00:10:40.640
she was like,
"Let me drop my secrets on you."

00:10:40.814 --> 00:10:42.424
See, I never got that.

00:10:42.598 --> 00:10:43.904
My dad died
before he could stop
being my dad

00:10:44.078 --> 00:10:46.123
and spill
all the family secrets.

00:10:46.297 --> 00:10:49.170
-[CELL PHONE BUZZES]
-I gotta get back to work.

00:10:49.344 --> 00:10:51.912
Hey. I want to talk to you
about our conversation
the other night.

00:10:52.086 --> 00:10:54.262
Yes.
I'm so glad you brought that up.

00:10:54.436 --> 00:10:57.526
I totally see your point
about Bruce Wayne and Batman.

00:10:57.700 --> 00:11:00.572
If you want something
that I can't give you,

00:11:00.747 --> 00:11:02.923
then I don't want
to waste your time.

00:11:03.097 --> 00:11:05.403
We're not wasting time.

00:11:06.404 --> 00:11:09.407
[EXHALES] I don't know
what's gonna happen,

00:11:09.581 --> 00:11:11.061
but right now, this is good,

00:11:11.235 --> 00:11:13.237
so let's just stay
in the right now.

00:11:14.543 --> 00:11:16.763
Yeah, this is good.

00:11:19.548 --> 00:11:21.376
I'll see you later?

00:11:21.550 --> 00:11:25.206
You know where I live.
'Cause you live there too. So...

00:11:29.384 --> 00:11:31.212
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:38.132 --> 00:11:40.047
ALMA: Ugh. I can't believe
we have to go to this thing.

00:11:40.221 --> 00:11:42.136
SAM: Yeah,
and it sucks that your sister
is getting married

00:11:42.310 --> 00:11:44.399
and your mom
is throwing her this party
and everyone's happy.

00:11:44.573 --> 00:11:45.530
ALMA: Exactly.

00:11:45.705 --> 00:11:46.880
SAM: [LAUGHS] I was kidding.

00:11:53.060 --> 00:11:54.714
Hi.

00:11:54.888 --> 00:11:56.411
I knew
I shouldn't have said anything.

00:11:56.585 --> 00:11:59.327
Well, I know you like it
when I wear make-up. So...

00:11:59.501 --> 00:12:00.894
Okay. Well, have fun

00:12:01.068 --> 00:12:02.591
embarrassing your sister
on her special night.

00:12:02.765 --> 00:12:04.288
This isn't her special night.

00:12:04.462 --> 00:12:06.421
Her special night
is the wedding.
This is dinner.

00:12:06.595 --> 00:12:08.423
This is also a special night.
There are multiple
special nights.

00:12:08.597 --> 00:12:10.251
She doesn't care.
You're the only one
who's gonna care.

00:12:13.558 --> 00:12:15.125
Always nice to see you, Sam.

00:12:15.299 --> 00:12:17.084
Ooh, Sam's getting
some love tonight.

00:12:17.258 --> 00:12:18.172
[CHUCKLES] Okay.

00:12:18.346 --> 00:12:19.477
Just come inside.

00:12:20.609 --> 00:12:22.132
[CAMILA SIGHS]

00:12:23.568 --> 00:12:26.006
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

00:12:30.662 --> 00:12:32.926
We can go whenever you're ready.

00:12:33.100 --> 00:12:35.580
Don't you think
we should at least
stay through the dinner portion

00:12:35.755 --> 00:12:37.669
of the dinner?

00:12:37.844 --> 00:12:40.324
Oh! Alma, love the 'stache!

00:12:40.498 --> 00:12:41.761
Thanks, Reed.

00:12:41.935 --> 00:12:43.414
Is this some rebellion
against Mom?

00:12:43.588 --> 00:12:45.590
-Not... Exactly.
-Exactly.

00:12:45.765 --> 00:12:48.071
-Good to see you again, Alma.
-Hey, Beth, how are you?

00:12:48.245 --> 00:12:50.770
Hey, haven't I see you before
on a Pringles can?!

00:12:50.944 --> 00:12:52.859
-[ALL LAUGHING]
-REED: Nice one, Dad.

00:12:53.033 --> 00:12:54.425
You getting the reaction
you were hoping for?

00:12:54.599 --> 00:12:56.297
-Yes.
-[glass clinks]

00:12:56.471 --> 00:12:59.822
Now that we're all here, um,
I'd like to propose a toast.

00:12:59.996 --> 00:13:04.522
To Becca Winograd-Diaz.
The love of my life.

00:13:04.696 --> 00:13:06.829
When we first got together,

00:13:07.003 --> 00:13:10.615
it was like
we were two puzzle pieces
spinning through the universe,

00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:14.271
and then click,
we found each other.

00:13:14.445 --> 00:13:16.621
-And the puzzle was complete.
-[BECCA CHUCKLES]

00:13:18.188 --> 00:13:20.669
It was only a two-piece puzzle.

00:13:20.843 --> 00:13:23.367
Like a puzzle for a little baby.

00:13:23.541 --> 00:13:26.109
But, uh, yeah.

00:13:26.283 --> 00:13:28.155
To Becca!
And the rest of our lives!

00:13:28.329 --> 00:13:30.200
I love you. Thank you.

00:13:30.374 --> 00:13:32.115
-ALMA: Cheers.
-BECCA: Cheers!

00:13:47.348 --> 00:13:48.392
Hey.

00:13:50.394 --> 00:13:51.656
I love you.

00:13:52.744 --> 00:13:53.963
I love you, too.

00:13:59.055 --> 00:14:00.274
We need to talk.

00:14:03.886 --> 00:14:06.802
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

00:14:06.976 --> 00:14:08.848
ALMA: Do you ever feel
like you're in a play?

00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:14.027
Except you're the only one
that knows it's a play.

00:14:14.201 --> 00:14:16.377
[LAUGHTER]

00:14:16.551 --> 00:14:17.944
And everyone else
is just playing the role

00:14:18.118 --> 00:14:19.075
they think
they're supposed to play,

00:14:19.249 --> 00:14:21.643
because that's what you do?

00:14:21.817 --> 00:14:24.080
And you're like,
"Hey, this is just a play.
We don't have to do this."

00:14:24.254 --> 00:14:26.343
And maybe we shouldn't.

00:14:28.824 --> 00:14:30.478
BECCA:
What are you talking about?

00:14:30.652 --> 00:14:31.914
I broke up with Sam.

00:14:32.088 --> 00:14:34.743
Oh, my God, are you okay?
What happened?

00:14:34.917 --> 00:14:37.528
[COUNTRY MUSIC
PLAYING ON STEREO]

00:14:38.660 --> 00:14:40.792
I know you don't
really remember,

00:14:40.967 --> 00:14:42.490
but Dad's mom was schizophrenic.

00:14:42.664 --> 00:14:43.795
I know.
What does that have to do
with anything?

00:14:43.970 --> 00:14:45.275
She was perfectly happy

00:14:45.449 --> 00:14:46.624
and then she got married
and made a family,

00:14:46.798 --> 00:14:48.452
because that's what you
did back then.

00:14:48.626 --> 00:14:51.325
And she ended up on lithium,
getting shock treatments,

00:14:51.499 --> 00:14:53.327
and shoving a broom handle
through the television set

00:14:53.501 --> 00:14:55.546
while her boys
watched Howdy Doody.

00:14:55.720 --> 00:14:58.549
Getting married
isn't what made her crazy.
She just had a bad brain.

00:14:58.723 --> 00:15:00.812
Yes, but if you know
you have a broken brain

00:15:00.987 --> 00:15:02.466
then why would you put
someone else through that?

00:15:02.640 --> 00:15:04.947
Okay. Tough love time?

00:15:05.121 --> 00:15:06.557
My God, you say that
like you're asking me,

00:15:06.731 --> 00:15:07.863
but I never agree
to "tough love time."

00:15:08.037 --> 00:15:09.604
I think
what is actually going on

00:15:09.778 --> 00:15:11.475
is your younger sister
is getting married before you,

00:15:11.649 --> 00:15:13.042
and you feel your life
slipping away.

00:15:13.216 --> 00:15:14.957
-No... That's not it.
-Hm? Yes.

00:15:15.131 --> 00:15:18.265
An amazing guy
wants to marry me,
and you're jealous.

00:15:18.439 --> 00:15:20.745
-Okay. Amazing?
-And it's okay, Alma.

00:15:20.920 --> 00:15:23.531
You realized that Sam
wasn't good enough for you,
and you broke up with him.

00:15:23.705 --> 00:15:25.750
That's not why I broke up
with Sam.

00:15:25.925 --> 00:15:28.753
-And it's okay
to want a better life.
-What are you talking about?

00:15:28.928 --> 00:15:31.887
I am talking about the fact
that you could be better,

00:15:32.061 --> 00:15:34.324
but you choose not to.

00:15:34.498 --> 00:15:35.760
Like,
instead of going back to school
and getting your B.A.,

00:15:35.935 --> 00:15:37.240
you work at a day care.

00:15:37.414 --> 00:15:39.373
-And you are so smart...
-[SCOFFS]

00:15:39.547 --> 00:15:42.637
...but you always, like,
make the losing choice
to, like, prove...

00:15:42.811 --> 00:15:44.508
I don't know
what you're trying to prove.

00:15:44.682 --> 00:15:47.555
But you don't have to be afraid
to move forward.

00:15:47.729 --> 00:15:50.340
I'm doing it, why can't you?

00:15:50.514 --> 00:15:53.430
[INHALES]
Can I try on your ring?

00:15:54.649 --> 00:15:55.693
Sure.

00:15:59.001 --> 00:16:02.004
[BREATHES DEEPLY, CHUCKLES]

00:16:02.178 --> 00:16:04.659
-My God!
-I know. I know. I know.

00:16:04.833 --> 00:16:07.879
This blood diamond does make me
feel special. Now I get it.

00:16:08.054 --> 00:16:09.359
-Okay, give it back to me.
Give it back!
-Hey!

00:16:09.533 --> 00:16:11.535
Shots of tequila.
Keep 'em coming.

00:16:11.709 --> 00:16:13.581
-You got it.
-Don't get wasted.

00:16:13.755 --> 00:16:14.930
We promised Mom
that we'd meet her
at church in the morning.

00:16:15.104 --> 00:16:16.279
You promised. I said I'd see.

00:16:16.453 --> 00:16:18.151
-I'm not doing shots.
-Yes, you are.

00:16:18.325 --> 00:16:22.851
Because your only sister
just got engaged!

00:16:23.025 --> 00:16:24.461
Hey, I'll take one with you.

00:16:28.161 --> 00:16:29.075
Salud.

00:16:29.249 --> 00:16:30.467
ALMA: Shit.

00:16:33.079 --> 00:16:35.124
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO]

00:16:36.430 --> 00:16:37.474
Whoo!

00:16:39.737 --> 00:16:41.870
ALMA: Okay, okay, okay.
Who's next?

00:16:42.044 --> 00:16:45.308
Did whoever stole
all your furniture
have a thing against pianos?

00:16:45.482 --> 00:16:48.659
That is not the answer
to my question, Tomás!

00:16:48.833 --> 00:16:50.226
Okay, I'm next.
I'm next, I'm next.

00:16:50.400 --> 00:16:52.446
-Ask me.
-Okay. Truth or Dare?

00:16:52.620 --> 00:16:54.274
-Truth.
-Okay.

00:16:54.448 --> 00:16:57.538
What are you most excited
about getting married... about?

00:16:57.712 --> 00:17:01.629
Oh, right. Okay.
Well, just, having sex
for the first time.

00:17:01.803 --> 00:17:04.762
Nuh-uh, shut up.
Are you seriously a virgin?

00:17:04.936 --> 00:17:06.155
She's kidding.

00:17:06.329 --> 00:17:07.635
Oh, good,
'cause I was gonna say

00:17:07.809 --> 00:17:08.723
you definitely do not seem
like a virgin.

00:17:08.897 --> 00:17:12.031
Well, what do I seem like?

00:17:12.205 --> 00:17:14.381
-Stop flirting!
-Ow! [LAUGHS]

00:17:14.555 --> 00:17:15.773
You're engaged, remember?

00:17:17.297 --> 00:17:18.472
Truth or dare?

00:17:18.646 --> 00:17:20.126
Dare.

00:17:20.300 --> 00:17:24.173
I dare you... to kiss my sis.

00:17:24.347 --> 00:17:25.435
-No.
-Yeah!

00:17:25.609 --> 00:17:27.524
-No!
-Yeah!

00:17:27.698 --> 00:17:28.569
It's cool,
you don't have to kiss me
if you don't want to.

00:17:28.743 --> 00:17:30.223
No, I want to, but I can't.

00:17:30.397 --> 00:17:33.356
ALMA: It's a game, Becca.
It's just a stupid game.

00:17:36.490 --> 00:17:39.275
Okay,
one small, tiny, dumb kiss.

00:17:44.889 --> 00:17:47.936
There you go.
Thank you. That's it.

00:17:48.110 --> 00:17:50.156
Boo! That sucks!

00:17:50.330 --> 00:17:51.853
[ALL LAUGHING]

00:17:52.027 --> 00:17:54.464
-That was like a Tío Oscar kiss.
-Ew, no, it wasn't.

00:17:54.638 --> 00:17:57.119
-Your Uncle Oscar
lip-kisses you?
-He does. He totally does.

00:17:57.293 --> 00:17:58.599
-It's super weird.
-[ALMA MUMBLING]

00:17:58.773 --> 00:18:00.775
I don't want to kiss you
like your Tío Oscar.

00:18:02.385 --> 00:18:03.430
Okay.

00:18:07.956 --> 00:18:09.610
[KISSING]

00:18:30.892 --> 00:18:32.415
[RETCHING]

00:18:54.611 --> 00:18:56.265
PRIEST: "Look at the birds
of the air;

00:18:56.439 --> 00:18:59.790
they do not sow or reap
or store away in barns,

00:18:59.964 --> 00:19:02.924
and yet our heavenly Father
feeds them.

00:19:03.098 --> 00:19:06.362
Are you not much more valuable
than they?"

00:19:06.536 --> 00:19:08.277
What does this mean?

00:19:08.451 --> 00:19:11.367
Does this mean
that we should not farm
and store away food?

00:19:11.541 --> 00:19:14.022
That we should blindly trust God
will provide for us?

00:19:14.196 --> 00:19:16.633
That we do nothing to provide
for ourselves?

00:19:18.635 --> 00:19:23.118
I was recently at a gathering
of several indigenous groups
from South and Central America.

00:19:23.292 --> 00:19:27.383
And one thing
these disparate groups
could agree on

00:19:27.557 --> 00:19:30.081
was that humans have lost
their connection with nature.

00:19:30.256 --> 00:19:34.173
In fact,
we have forgotten we are nature.

00:19:34.347 --> 00:19:38.307
And it is in rhythm with nature
that we are provided for.

00:19:38.481 --> 00:19:41.745
Through our not taking selfishly
more than we need,

00:19:41.919 --> 00:19:43.660
but instead recognizing...

00:19:43.834 --> 00:19:45.401
Where have you been?

00:19:45.575 --> 00:19:47.882
Who knows
where this girl's been.
Look at her.

00:19:48.056 --> 00:19:51.277
-PRIEST: ...than our small,
fearful desires.
-You know what, forget it.

00:19:51.451 --> 00:19:54.628
We are able to step
into this natural balance,

00:19:54.802 --> 00:19:58.762
-and live freely,
just like the birds.
-ALMA: Excuse me.

00:19:58.936 --> 00:20:01.722
Hey. Okay, look. Last night,
just having a little fun--

00:20:01.896 --> 00:20:03.985
Alma, this isn't funny.
This is my life.

00:20:04.159 --> 00:20:06.509
Hey, I didn't make you do
whatever it is you did
with that guy.

00:20:06.683 --> 00:20:08.729
I hope you feel really special
because you ruined something

00:20:08.903 --> 00:20:10.905
that was really beautiful
because it wasn't yours.

00:20:11.079 --> 00:20:12.385
Becca, I'm not trying
to ruin your life.

00:20:12.559 --> 00:20:13.473
Believe it or not,
I'm trying to help you.

00:20:13.647 --> 00:20:15.779
You don't want to marry Reed.

00:20:15.953 --> 00:20:17.346
Oh, right. I get it,
he's white, and he's rich,
so you don't like him.

00:20:17.520 --> 00:20:18.391
-That's not the point.
-Well, what is the point?

00:20:18.565 --> 00:20:19.696
'Cause we're broken people.

00:20:21.307 --> 00:20:24.179
Okay?
And broken people break people.

00:20:24.353 --> 00:20:27.356
No, I'm not broken, Alma.
I'm not.

00:20:27.530 --> 00:20:30.054
I'm really fucking happy,
and I wish that you would stop
telling me

00:20:30.229 --> 00:20:32.100
what you think is best for me
because I'm not you.

00:20:32.274 --> 00:20:34.233
-Okay...
-You are so insanely
self-involved.

00:20:34.407 --> 00:20:36.626
You don't even know
all the things
that are wrong with you.

00:20:36.800 --> 00:20:38.672
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

00:20:40.891 --> 00:20:42.241
No, I do.

00:20:43.894 --> 00:20:45.244
Trust me.

00:20:47.333 --> 00:20:49.073
You know what?
Here's your ring.

00:20:51.293 --> 00:20:52.816
You can try to hold onto it.

00:20:57.125 --> 00:20:59.170
-[TIRES SCREECHING]
-[CAR HORN HONKING]

00:20:59.345 --> 00:21:01.172
[SOBS]

00:21:02.304 --> 00:21:03.740
[GRUNTS, SOBS]

00:21:16.536 --> 00:21:17.580
Dad?

00:21:30.245 --> 00:21:33.901
[END THEME MUSIC PLAYING]